# Environment Variables

Copy to `.env.local`:

```env
# Supabase (required for production auth + sync)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Server-only: manager creates staff accounts from dashboard
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# ImgBB — product & logo image uploads (server-only)
# Get your key at https://api.imgbb.com/
IMGBB_API_KEY=your-imgbb-api-key

# App (production)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://valantino-pos.vercel.app

# Telegram — optional env fallback only.
# Primary: save Bot Token + Chat ID + Webhook from Settings UI (stored in Supabase settings key = telegram)
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_BOT_USERNAME=
TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
CRON_SECRET=
```

Without Supabase credentials the app cannot authenticate users. Business data syncs to Supabase when configured.
Production URL: https://valantino-pos.vercel.app
Telegram config is stored in the database (settings.key = 'telegram') from the Settings page.
